<h2>Create A Share</h2>

<form role="form" action="/shares/" method="post" class="form-inline">
  <div class="form-group">
    <label for="name">Share Name:</label>
    <input type="text" name="name" placeholder="Documents" class="form-control">
  </div>
  <button type="submit" class="btn btn-default">Create Share</button>
</form>

<div style="margin-top: 1ex">&nbsp;</div>

<p>The recommended name for the default user share is "Documents".</p>
<p>In future releases FogSync will define semantics for some specific share names.
If you use them for something else, future versions of FogSync may get confused.
These will be separate shares to allow you to select what you want to sync to
(e.g.) your phone.</p>

<p>My current guess as to what the names for special shares will be is:</p>
<dl>
  <dt>Contacts</dt>
  <dd>This will store your contacts, in vCard or some similar format.</dd>
  <dt>Calendar</dt>
  <dd>Your calendar events, in iCalendar or similar format.</dd>
  <dt>Email</dt>
  <dd>This wll store your electronic mail in Maildir or some similar format.</dd>
  <dt>Chats</dt>
  <dd>An archive of instant messages, SMS, etc.</dd>
</dl>

{{#if broken}}

<h3>Broken Shares</h3>

<p>These shares do not correctly decrypt. Either their metadata has become corrupted
or they were created with a different master key.</p>

<table class="table table-striped">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Share HMAC</th>
      <th>Actions</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
  {{#each broken}}
  <tr>
    <td>{{this}}</td>
    <td><button class="btn btn-danger delete-broken" {{bind-attr data-name="this"}}>
        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-remove"></span> Delete </button></td>
  </tr>
  {{/each}}
  </tbody>
</table>

{{/if}}
